    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - INSTALL - GEAR SHIFT LEVER HOUSING ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER HOUSING ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the shifting notches on the bars in the shifter housing are aligned in the neutral
                position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the gear shift lever housing on the shifter housing, fitting the lower end of the
                lever into the notches in the shifting block and yokes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024h8">Figure 178</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024h8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024h8" filename="../figg13/G13024h8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 178. Install Gear Shift Lever Housing on Shifter Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install attaching bolts, except the bolt at the left rear corner as this is used to secure
                the air line. Tighten bolts to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
